cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.GT

This paper belongs to the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence applied to finance. The use of reinforcement learning and Q-learning algorithms suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on money management and decision-making processes in retail banking suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Economics) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of probability estimation and simulation techniques suggests that it could be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
